Well - she used to - say of a - Saturday - night she'd got and - have a couple of drinks with him. But me mother, I used to get her her - 'course you was allowed to go in the pub when I was a lad, get her half a pint of stout a
nd in the winter time - she used to have them - small onions - baked in the oven. If she had a cold or anything like that. And the pair of us used to sit down and I'd have a cup of tea and I'd have me old onions, and she'd have her onions as well, and her
 glass of beer. Used to enjoy it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid2764714 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \lang2057\langfe1033\langnp2057\insrsid1983454\charrsid11870673 You fetched it for her?
